WEBVTT

00:01.569 --> 00:04.105
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:28.329 --> 00:30.831
Together:
We want food! We want food!

00:30.864 --> 00:32.500
MOM: It was a day
like any other,

00:32.533 --> 00:35.269
by which I mean just
as terrible as the rest.

00:35.303 --> 00:36.804
All I wanted for us to behave

00:36.837 --> 00:39.607
like a normal, civilized family
at meal times.

00:39.640 --> 00:42.310
I might as well have wished
for it to rain pancakes.

00:42.343 --> 00:44.145
And not just the ones the kids
made for breakfast.

00:44.178 --> 00:46.447
We want food!
We want --

00:46.480 --> 00:47.881
Kids, please!

00:47.915 --> 00:50.151
It needs to be way louder
to have any effect.

00:50.184 --> 00:51.319
We want food!

00:51.352 --> 00:52.520
We want food!

00:52.553 --> 00:53.921
Is that really necessary?

00:53.954 --> 00:55.523
But you work better
under pressure.

00:55.556 --> 00:56.824
Anyway, I helped.

00:56.857 --> 00:58.392
You were supposed
to salt the potatoes,

00:58.426 --> 00:59.427
boil the carrots,
and tenderize the meat.

00:59.460 --> 01:00.694
But instead...

01:00.728 --> 01:03.397
It's okay if it's not
perfect, honey.

01:03.431 --> 01:05.799
It's just nice to eat
together for once.

01:05.833 --> 01:06.834
[ Grumbles ]

01:06.867 --> 01:08.136
[ Sniffing ]

01:08.169 --> 01:09.503
Kids: We want food!

01:09.537 --> 01:10.871
Hmm.
Something's burning.
[ Sizzling ]

01:10.904 --> 01:13.241
Oh, it's just your eyes
burning a hole

01:13.274 --> 01:14.975
in the back of my head.

01:15.008 --> 01:16.244
Well, scratch that.

01:16.277 --> 01:17.745
It's your pot catching fire
because I distracted you.

01:17.778 --> 01:19.046
[ Smoke alarm beeping ]
[ Gasps ]

01:19.079 --> 01:20.414
Don't panic!

01:20.448 --> 01:22.082
In case of fire, you should
stop, drop, and roll!

01:22.116 --> 01:23.083
Okay!

01:23.117 --> 01:24.285
What the...?

01:24.318 --> 01:25.519
Somebody get a blanket!

01:25.553 --> 01:26.554
Leave it to me!

01:26.587 --> 01:27.855
[ Glass shatters ]

01:27.888 --> 01:30.191
Gumball,
grab the tablecloth.

01:30.224 --> 01:32.660
[ Beeping continues ]

01:32.693 --> 01:34.162
It's getting worse!

01:34.195 --> 01:36.430
[ Indistinct shouting ]

01:37.198 --> 01:39.500
I got this!

01:45.873 --> 01:46.874
[ All gasp ]

01:46.907 --> 01:48.041
[ Growls ]

01:48.075 --> 01:50.478
That was the moment
I asked myself,

01:50.511 --> 01:52.146
"How did it come to this?

01:52.180 --> 01:53.747
Where did I go wrong?"

01:53.781 --> 01:56.750
That's it.
It was the day I met him.

01:56.784 --> 01:59.753
I was on the way to the
tournament with Mom and Dad.

02:01.589 --> 02:04.625
Nicole, we need to talk
about your report card.

02:04.658 --> 02:06.327
But I got straight A's.

02:06.360 --> 02:08.496
Not here -- Gender.

02:08.529 --> 02:10.364
Uh, yeah,
that's because I'm female.

02:10.398 --> 02:12.433
Being a girl
is not an excuse.

02:12.466 --> 02:13.601
[ Horns blaring ]

02:13.634 --> 02:15.669
What is it
with this traffic?!

02:15.703 --> 02:17.338
Aah!
[ Horn blares ]

02:17.371 --> 02:19.473
Dad!
Now what am I gonna do?

02:19.507 --> 02:20.974
How much time have I got?

02:21.008 --> 02:23.844
54,321 minutes
until your graduation.

02:23.877 --> 02:28.282
374,582 minutes until you get
your diploma from law school.

02:28.316 --> 02:32.486
and 754,471 minutes
until you marry a doctor.

02:32.520 --> 02:34.388
I mean before
the tournament!

02:34.422 --> 02:36.390
Five minutes.
You'll make it if you run.

02:36.424 --> 02:38.025
[ Gasps ]

02:38.058 --> 02:39.927
And remember...

02:39.960 --> 02:42.363
I know. I know.
I love you, too.

02:42.396 --> 02:45.299
No, I was gonna say second place
is first place for losers,

02:45.333 --> 02:46.567
but, yeah, that too.

02:46.600 --> 02:48.101
Uh, uh [groans]

02:50.103 --> 02:52.540
[ Gasps ]

02:52.573 --> 02:54.942
[ Grunts ]
-[ Gasps ]

02:58.612 --> 03:02.115
Well, it took all day,
but I got the job done.

03:02.149 --> 03:02.983
[ Sighs ]

03:04.852 --> 03:07.255
Hey, do you want to hear
my song?

03:07.288 --> 03:09.189
Wait, you didn't answer my...

03:09.223 --> 03:10.057
Oh.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.662
Hey, girl,
you don't have to run.

03:14.695 --> 03:17.265
I ain't going nowhere.

03:17.298 --> 03:19.433
Mother nature is my doctor.

03:19.467 --> 03:21.902
Prescription hugs!
Prescription hugs!

03:21.935 --> 03:23.404
Hey, a moment of your time?

03:23.437 --> 03:25.072
[ Groaning ]

03:32.112 --> 03:33.447
Hey, you need a ride?

03:33.481 --> 03:35.015
[ Grunts ]

03:36.317 --> 03:38.386
Then I realized I was lost.

03:38.419 --> 03:39.553
Huh?

03:39.587 --> 03:41.322
YOUNG RICHARD:
Uh, hello?

03:41.355 --> 03:43.591
And that's when I saw him.

03:43.624 --> 03:45.693
A little help, please.

03:48.396 --> 03:49.663
[ Chuckles ]

03:49.697 --> 03:51.999
That was the moment.

03:52.032 --> 03:55.202
But what if I hadn't
turned right?

03:55.235 --> 03:56.737
Where would I be now?

03:58.572 --> 04:00.774
Well, it took all day...

04:02.343 --> 04:03.544
Hajime!

04:03.577 --> 04:05.879
[ Screaming ]

04:10.851 --> 04:13.587
Thank heavens she's gone.

04:15.689 --> 04:18.125
Okay, I'll try not to dwell
on what that says about me.

04:18.158 --> 04:21.595
Maybe I should have listened
to Banana Bob's song.

04:21.629 --> 04:22.963
Hey, do you want
to hear my song?

04:22.996 --> 04:24.164
Okay.

04:24.197 --> 04:26.734
[ Soothing music plays ]

04:30.137 --> 04:34.342
♪ Banana, nana

04:34.375 --> 04:35.343
[ Chuckles ]

04:35.376 --> 04:36.844
♪ Banana-na

04:36.877 --> 04:38.379
[ Laughs ]
You're funny.

04:38.412 --> 04:40.948
[ Humming wedding march ]
♪ Ba-na-na-na-na-na-na-na

04:40.981 --> 04:42.416
[ Laughs ]

04:42.450 --> 04:44.084
[ Humming "Happy Birthday" ]
♪ Ba-na-na-na-na-na

04:44.117 --> 04:45.753
♪ Ba-na-na-na-na-na
[ Whimpers ]

04:45.786 --> 04:47.455
[ Snoring ]

04:47.488 --> 04:49.022
Ba-na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na.

04:49.056 --> 04:50.858
[ Whimpering ]
Ba-na-na-na-na.

04:50.891 --> 04:54.362
Ba-na-na-na-na-na-na-na.

04:54.395 --> 04:57.798
Ba-na-na-na-na-na-na-na-na.
-Nicole? Are you okay?

04:57.831 --> 04:59.633
Ba-na-na-na-na!

04:59.667 --> 05:01.469
Ba-na-na-na-na!

05:01.502 --> 05:03.236
Ohh, banana-not.
Banana-na.

05:03.270 --> 05:05.272
Ohh. Better not.

05:05.305 --> 05:06.640
[ Zoom! ]

05:06.674 --> 05:07.841
But what about Harold?

05:07.875 --> 05:09.643
Hey, girl,
you don't have to run.

05:09.677 --> 05:11.178
Okay, what do you want?

05:11.211 --> 05:13.246
Have you lost weight?
Your head looks bigger.

05:13.280 --> 05:14.515
What?
Nothing.

05:14.548 --> 05:16.484
I just wanted to say I like
girls with really short legs.

05:16.517 --> 05:18.285
What?
What's wrong with my legs?

05:18.318 --> 05:20.020
Wait, are you doing
that creepy thing

05:20.053 --> 05:21.922
where guys criticize girls
to lower their confidence

05:21.955 --> 05:23.223
so they'll go out
with them?

05:23.256 --> 05:24.925
Your way too intelligent
for that kind of trick.

05:24.958 --> 05:26.326
Your parents
don't love you.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.696
[ Wedding march plays ]

05:28.729 --> 05:31.365
You look better
with the veil on.

05:31.399 --> 05:33.200
Hey!

05:34.568 --> 05:37.438
So, how do you
like the sushi?

05:37.471 --> 05:39.006
I-It took me hours.

05:39.039 --> 05:40.574
It's cold.

05:40.608 --> 05:43.243
Let me heat it up
for you.

05:43.276 --> 05:45.045
Is that hot enough for you?!
Is it?!

05:45.078 --> 05:48.516
Is it hot enough?!
Is it hot enough for you?!

05:48.549 --> 05:50.618
Mm, almost worth it.

05:50.651 --> 05:51.985
Hey -- Aah!

05:52.019 --> 05:54.422
Prescription hugs!
Prescription hugs!

05:54.455 --> 05:55.823
Hey, there.
[ Screech! ]

05:55.856 --> 05:57.725
Have you ever considered
using the power of hugs

05:57.758 --> 05:59.460
as an alternative
to modern medicine?

05:59.493 --> 06:00.894
Hmm.

06:00.928 --> 06:02.863
[ Bach's "Tocatta and Fugue
in D Minor" plays ]

06:02.896 --> 06:04.565
[ Thunder crashes ]

06:04.598 --> 06:05.999
Uh, makes sense.

06:06.033 --> 06:07.935
The hugs would only transmit
diseases faster.

06:07.968 --> 06:09.403
Hey, a moment
of your time?

06:09.437 --> 06:12.205
[ Grunting and groaning ]

06:12.239 --> 06:14.475
Wait, they say a single flap
of a butterfly's wing

06:14.508 --> 06:17.044
can cause a hurricane on
the other side of the world.

06:17.077 --> 06:18.746
So what would have happened
if I'd never stepped on --

06:18.779 --> 06:20.781
[ Choking ]

06:20.814 --> 06:23.216
Don't worry!
A hug will cure you!

06:23.250 --> 06:24.752
[ Bach's "Tocatta and Fugue
in D Minor" plays ]

06:24.785 --> 06:25.886
[ Thunder crashes ]

06:25.919 --> 06:27.254
Ohh, whatever.

06:27.287 --> 06:28.522
They only live
for a day anyway.

06:28.556 --> 06:29.523
[ Butterfly whimpers ]

06:29.557 --> 06:30.991
Hey, you need a ride?

06:31.024 --> 06:32.760
No --
Oh, wait, I do, actually.

06:32.793 --> 06:34.094
Uh, you got
a spare helmet?

06:34.127 --> 06:35.596
You don't need a helmet
when you're cool.

06:35.629 --> 06:37.097
[ Bach's "Tocatta and Fugue
in D Minor" plays ]

06:37.130 --> 06:38.999
I'm gonna have to
write the mayor

06:39.032 --> 06:41.134
about how dangerous
this park is.

06:41.168 --> 06:42.870
[ Grunts ]

06:44.137 --> 06:46.073
[ Panting ]

06:46.106 --> 06:47.775
Young Richard:
Uh, hello?

06:47.808 --> 06:49.743
A little help, please.

06:49.777 --> 06:51.479
[ Echoing ] I'm Richard.

06:51.512 --> 06:54.314
I guess there was
no other way around it.

06:54.347 --> 06:56.550
[ Chuckles ]
Nicole.

06:56.584 --> 06:57.785
I know.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.820
So...how?

06:59.853 --> 07:02.122
Well, I was feeding
a squirrel some nuts.

07:02.155 --> 07:03.591
[ Chuckles ]

07:03.624 --> 07:05.425
To see where he hides
all his nuts.

07:05.459 --> 07:06.560
Okay.

07:06.594 --> 07:07.895
And it worked
a little too well.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.396
Okay, don't move.

07:09.429 --> 07:10.464
Aah!

07:10.498 --> 07:12.466
Aah! No, no, no, no,
please!

07:14.167 --> 07:16.604
[ Chuckles ] Okay.
I've got to run now.

07:16.637 --> 07:17.738
Why?

07:17.771 --> 07:19.072
To compete.

07:19.106 --> 07:19.940
Why?

07:19.973 --> 07:21.341
'Cause I have to fight.

07:21.374 --> 07:22.309
Why?

07:22.342 --> 07:24.645
Because I have
to be the best.

07:24.678 --> 07:25.846
Why?

07:25.879 --> 07:27.715
So people will like me?

07:27.748 --> 07:29.717
But lots of people
already like you.

07:29.750 --> 07:32.352
[ Scoffs ] Really?
Like who?

07:34.488 --> 07:35.656
[ Bell chiming ]

07:35.689 --> 07:37.725
[ Gasps ]
It's 2:00 already!

07:37.758 --> 07:39.126
I'm too late!

07:39.159 --> 07:40.761
Ohh!

07:40.794 --> 07:42.763
I've got to go home
empty-handed.

07:42.796 --> 07:46.767
Not quite empty-handed.
You have...a nut.

07:46.800 --> 07:49.269
[ Sniffles ]
Huh?

07:49.302 --> 07:50.804
Half a nut?

07:50.838 --> 07:51.705
[ Chuckles ]

07:51.739 --> 07:53.273
[ Crunch! ]

07:53.306 --> 07:55.342
[ Crunch! ]

07:55.375 --> 07:57.044
Hmm.

07:57.077 --> 07:59.713
What would you do
if you were me?

07:59.747 --> 08:01.549
If I had done everything
you've done?

08:01.582 --> 08:03.116
Sleep till I'm 40.

08:03.150 --> 08:04.084
[ Chuckles ]

08:04.117 --> 08:05.919
I mean, what should I do
with my life?

08:05.953 --> 08:09.089
Hmm.
Maybe start living it.

08:10.591 --> 08:13.861
[ Soft piano music plays ]

08:58.906 --> 09:01.408
[ Music continues ]

09:22.696 --> 09:25.198
[ Music continues ]

09:28.068 --> 09:30.904
[ Music continues ]

10:09.142 --> 10:12.145
[ Music continues ]

10:36.636 --> 10:39.639
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

10:39.673 --> 10:44.044
Actually, you know what,
I wouldn't change a thing.

10:44.077 --> 10:46.613
[ Laughs ]

10:48.982 --> 10:50.150
Food fight!

10:50.183 --> 10:51.284
Oh, no, little man.

10:51.318 --> 10:53.420
This is a food war!

10:53.453 --> 10:56.990
[ Laughter ]
